Susan Fairchild, member of the board.

39
00:03:05,156 --> 00:03:06,857
Ken Kraus, member of the board.

40
00:03:07,398 --> 00:03:09,399
May Makibrek, member of the board.

41
00:03:09,900 --> 00:03:13,603
And Russ Rossetti, member of the Friends of Chevalier board of directors.

42
00:03:14,443 --> 00:03:20,028
You know, May, little known fact, was a Mustang Hall of Famer.

43
00:03:21,015 --> 00:03:21,896
back some years ago.

44
00:03:22,376 --> 00:03:22,776
Right, May?

45
00:03:23,497 --> 00:03:24,037
Where is May?

46
00:03:24,177 --> 00:03:24,677
May, where are you?

47
00:03:25,057 --> 00:03:25,858
You're up over here.

48
00:03:27,439 --> 00:03:28,620
Mustang Hall of Famer.

49
00:03:30,141 --> 00:03:34,183
May was the founding member of the Friends of Chevalier and Gene Mack Gymnasium.

50
00:03:35,464 --> 00:03:36,064
Cachet.

51
00:03:36,745 --> 00:03:47,331
It was the brainchild of May, meeting with a few people in the community regarding the arts, that put together Cachet, the Coalition for Art, Culture, and Healthy Economy.

52
00:03:48,211 --> 00:03:50,233
And, you know, May won't say it, but

53
00:03:51,056 --> 00:04:04,164
Those were May's ideas originally back many, many years ago to put organizations together, to link the community up, and pull in all different backgrounds in order to move this community forward.

54
00:04:05,024 --> 00:04:13,889
While promoting the arts is a main goal of CACHE, it also aims to bolster the local economy at the same time.

55
00:04:14,409 --> 00:04:20,593
Looking ahead, we are hoping to create a more vibrant arts and cultural scene in Method, which in turn

56
00:04:20,989 --> 00:04:23,931
will promote economic development, May Makibrek said.

57
00:04:25,031 --> 00:04:29,975
That part of it cannot be overlooked and it is what we feel sets the group apart.

58
00:04:31,535 --> 00:04:36,158
We all work together as equals with one big exception, John Anderson said.

59
00:04:37,079 --> 00:04:43,763
May Makibrek is really the driving force and she has been so enthusiastic and youthful and full of ideas.

60
00:04:44,203 --> 00:04:49,827
You need a person like that if a coalition such as this has any chance of surviving, which it is

61
00:04:50,870 --> 00:04:52,191
a good sign for us.

62
00:04:54,552 --> 00:04:56,694
May served as the President of Springstep.

63
00:04:57,675 --> 00:05:03,618
She also served on the Board of Directors for Brooks Estate's Land Trust.

64
00:05:04,859 --> 00:05:08,622
May was recognized by the Chamber of Commerce as Citizen of the Year.

65
00:05:10,298 --> 00:05:31,269
Who can forget May's article which appeared in the March 14, 2014 edition of the Method transcript honoring Method Olympic champion Mary Carew Armstrong for National Women's History Month, or the countless letters to the editor in which May offered support to local organizations.

66
00:05:33,850 --> 00:05:39,093
As we all know, May was part of a lot of different civic groups, but she was also very vocal on the issues.

67
00:05:40,207 --> 00:05:43,729
And May, she wasn't a wallflower.

68
00:05:43,889 --> 00:05:45,069
She let it be known.

69
00:05:45,749 --> 00:05:47,790
She let it be known where she stood in an issue.

70
00:05:48,611 --> 00:05:55,554
And if there was an issue that was confronting the residents of this community, you better believe May was at that podium.

71
00:05:56,614 --> 00:06:00,736
I remember the night the Medford Public Library was experiencing roof leaks.

72
00:06:01,516 --> 00:06:02,757
And guess who was at the podium?

73
00:06:04,487 --> 00:06:21,772
We have very, very dedicated people who are here tonight, members of the staff of the library, just hoping that the ceiling tiles in the building that they're working wouldn't fall in on their head, said Mae Mockeybrook, president of the Medford Coalition for the Arts at the council meeting.

74
00:06:22,252 --> 00:06:23,212
This is disgraceful.

75
00:06:25,633 --> 00:06:29,054
We often remember the debate with art funding in the budget.

76
00:06:29,863 --> 00:06:38,470
The city never funded arts in the budget, and a few years ago, this council offered a resolution to put arts in the budget, and May was at the podium once again.

77
00:06:39,051 --> 00:06:42,934
I think it's fair to say we're in an arts revolution, said May Makibrek.

78
00:06:43,414 --> 00:06:44,335
Medford has changed.

79
00:06:44,755 --> 00:06:46,717
We are no longer a streetcar suburb.

80
00:06:47,237 --> 00:06:48,498
We're a vibrant community.

81
00:06:48,999 --> 00:06:54,243
We have a great deal to offer, and there is an arts movement going on at the present time.

82
00:06:57,157 --> 00:07:01,019
Several years back, we had the Brooks Estates bond proposal that was before us.

83
00:07:01,599 --> 00:07:03,600
Quite a contentious issue for some.

84
00:07:04,741 --> 00:07:06,582
May, again, was at the podium.

85
00:07:07,102 --> 00:07:12,865
The Brooks Estates has been treated by the city like an orphan, said Meffitt resident May Marky-Brick.

86
00:07:15,027 --> 00:07:19,469
In 2010, community leaders were pushing to build up the Chevalier Theater.

87
00:07:20,610 --> 00:07:25,132
May stated, now that the problem is not so much the condition of the theater,

88
00:07:25,689 --> 00:07:31,472
which like any property requires ongoing maintenance, but the underutilization of the Chevalier Theater, she said.

89
00:07:31,992 --> 00:07:44,419
How much longer are we going to talk, continue to see a valuable asset in our community be underutilized and waste the opportunity to have Chevalier Theater become an engine of economic development in Medford Square?

90
00:07:47,140 --> 00:07:52,503
These are just a few of the things that I recall May working on over the years.

91
00:07:53,076 --> 00:08:01,099
as a community activist, as someone who wholeheartedly cared about the children of this community.

92
00:08:01,479 --> 00:08:09,343
You couldn't find anyone more responsive to the needs of the Boys and Girls Club, which is on Forest Street, than May.

93
00:08:10,083 --> 00:08:15,205
The arts movement, I think, May was the art movement for a number of years.

94
00:08:19,247 --> 00:08:22,248
And it's only appropriate tonight that we take the time to

95
00:08:23,193 --> 00:08:24,853
And I see this audience is filled.

96
00:08:24,933 --> 00:08:27,634
It's not many times that this audience gets filled.

97
00:08:27,714 --> 00:08:39,237
And it's my distinct honor and pleasure to thank my friend, May Makibrek, for her many years of dedicated service.

98
00:08:40,237 --> 00:08:42,858
And I know some members of the council want to speak.

99
00:08:43,358 --> 00:08:44,838
I'd just like to read the citation.

100
00:08:45,359 --> 00:08:47,639
And May, we have a few more speeches, if you don't mind.

101
00:08:48,759 --> 00:08:51,100
There's a nice comfy seat next to you if you want to sit down.

102
00:08:53,028 --> 00:09:11,281
It says the Meffitt City Council takes pleasure in awarding this council accommodation to Mae Makibrek in recognition of her 25 years of distinguished service as founder and member of the Friends of Chevalier Auditorium and GMAC Gymnasium, signed May 16th by Council President Richard Caviello and Vice President Michael J. Mox.

103
00:09:45,667 --> 00:09:47,248
Thank you, Councilor Marks.

104
00:09:48,489 --> 00:09:57,694
I'm just going to do a little word checking and make sure that I did say all those things.

105
00:09:58,274 --> 00:10:06,219
Well, this is a very special moment, and I appreciate all of you have come here this evening.

106
00:10:07,199 --> 00:10:09,761
When President Carviello called me,

107
00:10:10,632 --> 00:10:12,193
about coming here tonight.

108
00:10:12,914 --> 00:10:15,195
I thought he was going to ask me to be on a subcommittee.

109
00:10:17,697 --> 00:10:20,839
And I was going to have to say, I'm sorry.

110
00:10:23,321 --> 00:10:39,572
At any rate, in accepting this very, very wonderful tribute, I also have to give a lot of credit

111
00:10:40,328 --> 00:10:52,634
to all of the people who have been working on the Friends of Chevalier for the past 25 years, those past and those present, some of which are here in the chamber tonight.

112
00:10:54,275 --> 00:11:09,362
And thinking back about that early time, I would just like to remember a few of our dear friends who are probably looking down on us this evening.

113
00:11:10,466 --> 00:11:20,369
And that would be Teresa Cerullo, wife of Michael Cerullo, and John Nostry.

114
00:11:22,589 --> 00:11:29,611
And there may be others that I hope I haven't overlooked.

115
00:11:30,551 --> 00:11:37,973
Dick Oba, who were very, very much a part of the early days when we

116
00:11:38,938 --> 00:11:40,439
establish the Friends of Chevalier.

117
00:11:41,540 --> 00:11:50,805
And over the years, uh, the group has worked very diligently and very quietly, but has accomplished a great deal.

118
00:11:51,886 --> 00:12:03,593
In fact, in addition to being advocates for the theater and the Boys and Girls Club for these many years, they also raised a considerable amount of money.

119
00:12:04,813 --> 00:12:07,215
And believe it or not, that would be

120
00:12:08,217 --> 00:12:11,439
more than $350,000.

121
00:12:21,284 --> 00:12:37,573
One of the major grants that was given to the Friends was from the Cummings Foundation, which is a local philanthropic

122
00:12:38,308 --> 00:12:44,750
philanthropic organization by Bill Cummings and his wife.

123
00:12:46,211 --> 00:12:52,052
As you know, the property here adjoining us is owned by the Cummings people.

124
00:12:52,993 --> 00:13:02,076
So they gave $100,000 to add staff to the Boys and Girls Club.

125
00:13:02,896 --> 00:13:06,357
And I have to say that I'm very, very proud

126
00:13:06,868 --> 00:13:12,592
that the friends were a big part of the Boys and Girls Club coming here to Medford.

127
00:13:14,714 --> 00:13:16,715
They have been extremely successful.

128
00:13:19,217 --> 00:13:29,284
They still have a waiting list in spite of the additional money that they received from the Cummings people to add instructional staff.

129
00:13:30,224 --> 00:13:36,529
So we have been quietly working away over the years, and I just hope that

130
00:13:37,187 --> 00:13:46,631
Uh, those of you at some time may consider giving a small contribution because it's always very, very welcome.

131
00:13:47,591 --> 00:14:02,016
And I want to, uh, recognize as council marks did the current members on the board and to wish you good luck going forward.

132
00:14:02,377 --> 00:14:03,297
Thank you all very much.

133
00:14:20,756 --> 00:14:22,577
Thank you, Vice President Marks.

134
00:14:23,137 --> 00:14:27,680
I don't want to put you on the spot any longer, Mae, but I think a few of us just want to say a few words.

135
00:14:27,700 --> 00:14:33,263
Councilman Marks did a great job announcing you and taking quotes.

136
00:14:33,323 --> 00:14:33,823
That was great.

137
00:14:35,330 --> 00:14:38,931
From my standpoint, you've been a true leader in this community.

138
00:14:38,971 --> 00:14:51,293
You've done such wonderful things that so many people have benefited from, families and every resident in this community has benefited from your work with the Chevalier and Cachet and everything else you were involved in.

139
00:14:52,013 --> 00:14:59,894
The fact that you did it because you love this city and you wanted to make it better means a lot and I look up to you, May, and I wish you the best and good luck in your retirement.

140
00:15:00,134 --> 00:15:00,454
Thank you.

141
00:15:02,935 --> 00:15:03,715
Councilor Del Rosso.

142
00:15:04,836 --> 00:15:05,658
Thank you, Mr. Chairman.

143
00:15:05,879 --> 00:15:08,666
I want to also congratulate you, May.

144
00:15:09,869 --> 00:15:11,352
I want to thank you for your energy.

145
00:15:12,550 --> 00:15:26,896
Your selfless devotion to the city, your generosity to give of your spirit and your energy and yourself to so many commitments is tough, and we thank you.

146
00:15:27,837 --> 00:15:31,778
And I hope you keep going and going till you get it right.

147
00:15:32,219 --> 00:15:33,039
So keep at it.

148
00:15:33,719 --> 00:15:34,940
Practice makes perfect.

149
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:37,421
I'm not taking the city.

150
00:15:37,461 --> 00:15:37,701
Good.

151
00:15:38,881 --> 00:15:39,262
Thank you.

152
00:15:39,402 --> 00:15:40,182
Councilor Felico.

153
00:15:40,382 --> 00:15:41,583
Thank you, Mr. Chairman.

154
00:15:42,977 --> 00:15:45,678
May, I just want to say thank you and congratulations.

155
00:15:45,698 --> 00:15:50,540
You have been a true role model when it comes to civic engagement and people getting involved.

156
00:15:51,181 --> 00:15:53,942
And you're someone that people can look up to.

157
00:15:54,002 --> 00:15:57,303
I mean, you've been involved with so much throughout our city.

158
00:15:57,323 --> 00:16:02,165
And I just want to say thank you for your years of involvement and for your contributions to the community and good luck.

159
00:16:02,265 --> 00:16:02,606
Thank you.

160
00:16:04,286 --> 00:16:05,587
Council President Caviello.

161
00:16:06,111 --> 00:16:07,051
Thank you, Mr. Vice President.

162
00:16:07,531 --> 00:16:10,072
May, you and I have been friends for many years in this community.

163
00:16:10,092 --> 00:16:11,972
You and I have worked on a lot of projects together.

164
00:16:11,992 --> 00:16:14,293
And I don't know what to say.

165
00:16:14,313 --> 00:16:21,915
You know, you've always been ahead of the curve on a lot of issues when people, when they weren't popular, you were there to push them.

166
00:16:22,335 --> 00:16:25,376
I was there when you received your Citizen of the Year award.

167
00:16:25,396 --> 00:16:28,016
I was very proud to be in the room that night.

168
00:16:28,076 --> 00:16:31,257
And again, I don't think you'll ever retire.

169
00:16:33,116 --> 00:16:42,041
I know, though you say you're going to retire, I know we'll be seeing you around the city, and your voices will be heard long after your retirement again.

170
00:16:42,361 --> 00:16:47,905
May I thank you for your years of service to this city, and please continue doing the things you do.

171
00:16:47,945 --> 00:16:48,245
Thank you.

172
00:16:49,006 --> 00:16:49,226
Thank you.

173
00:16:49,626 --> 00:16:50,526
Councilor Scott Pelley.

174
00:16:51,807 --> 00:16:56,370
As a fellow Mustang Hall of Fame member, I look at my

175
00:16:59,530 --> 00:17:02,532
fellow leader and thank you for everything you do.

176
00:17:02,613 --> 00:17:26,051
I think that my council colleagues have said so much and there's not much more that I can add but just thank you and really to reach out to the rest of the community and say this is who we should emulate because Meffitt's a great city to live in and it's people like yourself who give so much and ask for so little and

177
00:17:28,599 --> 00:17:34,943
I hope someone really sees that torch and runs with it, as you're such a great role model.

178
00:17:34,963 --> 00:17:35,763
So thank you so much.

179
00:17:35,783 --> 00:17:38,945
Thank you.

180
00:17:39,025 --> 00:17:39,766
And Councilor Knight.

181
00:17:40,406 --> 00:17:41,667
Councilor Marks, thank you very much.

182
00:17:41,707 --> 00:17:43,168
And Mae, congratulations.

183
00:17:43,428 --> 00:17:45,829
I could say the same thing that my councilors have all said.

184
00:17:46,329 --> 00:17:47,330
I echo their sentiment.

185
00:17:47,930 --> 00:17:51,973
I am wondering, however, what you get for 25 years of service.

186
00:17:52,013 --> 00:17:52,653
Is it a watch?

187
00:17:53,053 --> 00:17:55,235
Do they give you a watch from the Cheville Air Commission?

188
00:17:56,665 --> 00:17:58,127
Nice, that's pretty good.

189
00:17:58,467 --> 00:17:59,688
That's an incentive right there.

190
00:18:00,769 --> 00:18:01,670
May, congratulations.

191
00:18:01,730 --> 00:18:02,591
I wish you the best of luck.

192
00:18:02,611 --> 00:18:04,913
Thank you very much for all you've done for the city and for his service.

193
00:18:06,014 --> 00:18:06,254
Thank you.

194
00:18:06,294 --> 00:18:07,555
And if I could just read this letter.

195
00:18:07,896 --> 00:18:13,421
Tonight we received a letter from the Meffitt Brooks Estates Land Trust, dated May 12th, 2017.

196
00:18:13,621 --> 00:18:21,368
It says, dear President Caviello, we are delighted the Meffitt City Council is honoring May Makibrick.

197
00:18:21,968 --> 00:18:29,673
The Meffitt-Brooks Estates Land Trust's M-Belt is deeply appreciative of all Mae Makibrek has done on behalf of our beloved Brooks Estates.

198
00:18:30,253 --> 00:18:32,135
She has been with us for almost two decades.

199
00:18:32,735 --> 00:18:38,038
The time we have spent so far to bring back this unique community asset to full public benefit.

200
00:18:38,679 --> 00:18:44,783
Her insights, energy, wise counsel, and steadfastness have been invaluable to us over the years.

201
00:18:45,343 --> 00:18:51,427
Mae has brought a unique blend of both traditional and new Meffitt to the table, and her enthusiasm and passion

202
00:18:51,850 --> 00:18:53,831
embody all that is good about our community.

203
00:18:54,271 --> 00:18:54,912
We will miss her.

204
00:18:55,452 --> 00:18:56,292
Happy birthday, May.

205
00:18:56,753 --> 00:19:03,876
We wish May all the best on her retirement from most of, and that's in parentheses, public life here in Method.

206
00:19:04,517 --> 00:19:10,960
Although we are sure we'll see her around town, we intend to honor her in our own way at one of our events this summer.

207
00:19:11,260 --> 00:19:14,602
So we hope she is ready to be embarrassed once again.

208
00:19:15,142 --> 00:19:18,144
Thank you for your continued support of the Brooks Estates.

209
00:19:18,544 --> 00:19:20,405
With best wishes, Tom Lincoln,

210
00:19:20,815 --> 00:19:22,816
President of the Brooks Estates Land Trust.

211
00:19:24,777 --> 00:19:25,477
Thank you very much.

212
00:19:25,537 --> 00:19:26,058
Thank you again.

213
00:19:26,078 --> 00:19:33,561
Mr. President.

214
00:19:33,581 --> 00:19:34,082
Mr. President.

215
00:19:41,365 --> 00:19:43,046
We do have one other paper up here.

216
00:19:44,347 --> 00:19:45,587
That's May related.

217
00:19:45,627 --> 00:19:46,468
May, don't go too far.

218
00:19:50,673 --> 00:19:52,374
Okay, motions, orders, and resolutions.

219
00:19:52,454 --> 00:19:56,377
Paper 17-449, offered by President Caviello.

220
00:19:56,897 --> 00:20:06,304
Be resolved, the Meffitt City Council and the City of Meffitt celebrate and wish, may mock your breath, a happy birthday.

221
00:20:19,936 --> 00:20:25,718
